AWKA – Four persons were al­legedly killed when gunmen reportedly attacked herders’ camp in Ndiukwuenu Com­munity in Orumba North Local Government Area of Anambra State. It was gathered that gun­men well equipped with guns and machete alleged­ly raided a Fulani camp at Ndiukwuenu Community, killing four persons and carting away 60 cattle in the process. A statement by the Miyet­ti Allah Cattle Breeders As­sociation of Nigeria lament­ed the incessant attacks of herdsmen camps in the state. -Advertisement- The Zonal chairman of the Miyetti Allah Cattle Breeders Association, Al­haji Gidado Soddiki, said the gunmen struck on May 30, 2022, by 7:00 p.m. The association there­fore noted that it not only appreciated the govern­ment and security agen­cies, it also sought for quick intervention to stop the killings. The MACBAN zonal chairman disclosed that the four persons killed were Mohammed Idris, Sale Idris, Abdulmumini Idris and Musa Idris but according to him, only the corpses of Mohammed Id­ris and Sale Idris were seen while the other persons were not seen. When contacted the Police Public Relations Officer of the Anambra State Police Command, DSP Ikenga Tochi, said the command has not received an official report on the in­cident.